  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n5. Regulated Industries\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Gambling\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n\n6. Prevention Strategies\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Independent audits\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigations\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
